links.title: CVS Health to Invest in Affordable Housing and Expand No-Cost Preventive Health Screenings in Orlando
links.description: WOONSOCKET, R.I., Nov. 10, 2020 /PRNewswire/ -- CVS Health (NYSE: CVS) today announced it will invest in 116 units of affordable housing and expand its no-cost preventive health screening program to Orlando as part of the company's commitment of nearly $600 million over five years to address racial inequity and social determinants of health in Black communities.

$BYND issues:

- Low Foodservice revs (especially International channel) due to COVID (y/y comparison skewed due to Canada revs moved from US revs segment to International Revs segment starting Jan 1, 2020)
- COGS higher due to higher volumes but $1.8M inventory write-off & product repackaging which also contributed to lowered gross profits & margins
- R&D up 39.1% + SG&A Expenses up 60.2% (marketing, compensation, legal fees & insurance costs)

Fiscal discipline required & increase expansion into International Foodservice channel (19K outlets vs 42K US outlets) 

Catalyst: $MCD McPlant; Beyond Burger 3.0; Golden Krust Jamaican Meat Pattie (Lizzo favorite); 7K $CVS Health stores to offer Beyond Burger & 5K locations to offer Beyond Meatballs; Intros Sausage links in Oct; Expanded distribution to 5K locations at Walmart, Kroger, Costco & Super Target in Sept; & No Asian 2nd wave.

TAM: $1.4T Global Meat category ($270B US Meat category)
